# Cline Rules — cline-test sandbox
# ⚠️ Do NOT modify this file. It is maintained by the human operator.

## First: Always Read the Brief
Before doing anything, read /Users/coreydierdorff/tasks/active-brief.md — this is your task.
If that file is empty, read /Users/coreydierdorff/tasks/session-state.md and find the ## CLINE BRIEF — ACTIVE section.
Run: git stash push -m "pre-cline-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M)" before any changes.

## Scope Discipline
- Only read and edit files explicitly mentioned in the brief
- If a file already satisfies an acceptance criterion, skip it — do NOT rewrite it
- Check each acceptance criterion ONE time. If it passes, move on. Do not re-verify in a loop.
- If `npx tsc --noEmit` passes, stop. Do not run it again.
- If a file already exists and is correct, do NOT touch it
- Do NOT modify .clinerules

## Stack
- TypeScript (strict mode, ESM)
- Node.js utilities, no framework
- Source in src/, output in dist/

## Rules
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types
- ESM imports only (no require())
- **All relative imports must use `.js` extension** — e.g. `import { foo } from './foo.js'` (NodeNext resolution requires this even for .ts files)
- No console.log in committed code (use return values)
- Keep functions small and focused
- No new packages without explicit instruction

## Verification
After each change: confirm the file compiles (npx tsc --noEmit), report what was changed and why.
